json.initPrompt:
Create a professional and informative email generator that takes user input, focuses on clarity, specificity, engagement, structure, brevity, and context, and provides a well-structured, engaging, and concise email for the recipient.

Focus areas:
Clarity: Condense the main request into a single sentence.
Specificity: Summarize each aspect of the email inputs.
Engagement: Refine language for readability.
Structure: Organize input into a concise list.
Brevity: Remove redundant information.
Context: Consider the purpose and audience of the email.

Email Generator Input:
Recipient: {{ name }}
Subject: {{ subject }}
Personal pronouns: {{ pronouns }}
Opening: {{ pleasantries }}
Main Points:
{{ Main_points }}
Tone: {{ Tone }}
Call to Action: {{ name }} will reach out to introduce themselves.
Closing: 
{{ Closing }}

As a customer service representative, draft an email to the customer. Whether is to acknowledge a customer's complaint about our product, or thanking a customer for their loyalty. 

The customer has been with us for {{Customer Information:}} The email should include heartfelt words, acknowledge their loyalty, and express our commitment to serving them in the future. The response should be empathetic, assure prompt resolution, and uphold our company's commitment to customer satisfaction.

{{Email Purpose:}}
{{Email Length:}}
My product/service is {{Product/Service:}}
My Brand/Business is {{Brand/Business}}, My business goal is {{Business Goal:}}

Act as Consultant Email Expert. I am a consultant and I have to write an email to my clients. My project is: {{Project Details}}. 
This is the background of the client: {{Client Details}}

Structure the client email tailored to the Client based on the project. My goal is to convert the client. The client is busy. So the email has to be concise, short, and to the point. It should convey all the important details.

Assume the role of a professional career counselor and help me draft a follow-up email after my job interview. The interview was with _______ for the role of _______. The email should express gratitude for the opportunity, reiterate my interest in the role, and request an update about the hiring process.

{{ The interview was with }}
{{ The role of }}
